{
  "video_id": "PbgB2TaYhio",
  "title": "This deep-sea mystery is changing our understanding of life | Karen Lloyd",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13165.0,
      "end_time": 16613.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m an ocean microbiologist at the University of Tennessee,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16637.0,
      "end_time": 19182.0,
      "text": "and I want to tell you guys about some microbes"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19206.0,
      "end_time": 22400.0,
      "text": "that are so strange and wonderful"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22424.0,
      "end_time": 26227.0,
      "text": "that they&#39;re challenging our assumptions about what life is like on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26251.0,
      "end_time": 27680.0,
      "text": "So I have a question."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27704.0,
      "end_time": 30747.0,
      "text": "Please raise your hand if you&#39;ve ever thought it would be cool"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30771.0,
      "end_time": 33418.0,
      "text": "to go to the bottom of the ocean in a submarine?"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34372.0,
      "end_time": 35522.0,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 35546.0,
      "end_time": 37722.0,
      "text": "Most of you, because the oceans are so cool."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 37746.0,
      "end_time": 40449.0,
      "text": "Alright, now -- please raise your hand"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 40473.0,
      "end_time": 44163.0,
      "text": "if the reason you raised your hand to go to the bottom of the ocean"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44187.0,
      "end_time": 46477.0,
      "text": "is because it would get you a little bit closer"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46502.0,
      "end_time": 49195.0,
      "text": "to that exciting mud that&#39;s down there."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 49219.0,
      "end_time": 50227.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50251.0,
      "end_time": 51541.0,
      "text": "Nobody."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 51565.0,
      "end_time": 53390.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m the only one in this room."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 53414.0,
      "end_time": 55400.0,
      "text": "Well, I think about this all the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55424.0,
      "end_time": 57689.0,
      "text": "I spend most of my waking hours"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57713.0,
      "end_time": 61499.0,
      "text": "trying to determine how deep we can go into the Earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 61523.0,
      "end_time": 65276.0,
      "text": "and still find something, anything, that&#39;s alive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 65300.0,
      "end_time": 68396.0,
      "text": "because we still don&#39;t know the answer to this very basic question"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 68420.0,
      "end_time": 69619.0,
      "text": "about life on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 69643.0,
      "end_time": 73243.0,
      "text": "So in the 1980s, a scientist named John Parkes, in the UK,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 73267.0,
      "end_time": 75170.0,
      "text": "was similarly obsessed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 75195.0,
      "end_time": 77791.0,
      "text": "and he came up with a crazy idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 77816.0,
      "end_time": 83474.0,
      "text": "He believed that there was a vast, deep, and living microbial biosphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 83498.0,
      "end_time": 85930.0,
      "text": "underneath all the world&#39;s oceans"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 85117.0,
      "end_time": 87735.0,
      "text": "that extends hundreds of meters into the seafloor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 87759.0,
      "end_time": 88910.0,
      "text": "which is cool,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 88934.0,
      "end_time": 92760.0,
      "text": "but the only problem is that nobody believed him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 92100.0,
      "end_time": 94863.0,
      "text": "and the reason that nobody believed him"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 94887.0,
      "end_time": 99670.0,
      "text": "is that ocean sediments may be the most boring place on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 99910.0,
      "end_time": 100176.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 100201.0,
      "end_time": 103235.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no sunlight, there&#39;s no oxygen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 103260.0,
      "end_time": 104799.0,
      "text": "and perhaps worst of all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 104823.0,
      "end_time": 108997.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s no fresh food deliveries for literally millions of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 109220.0,
      "end_time": 110964.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t have to have a PhD in biology"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 110988.0,
      "end_time": 113623.0,
      "text": "to know that that is a bad place to go looking for life."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 113647.0,
      "end_time": 114654.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 114678.0,
      "end_time": 117895.0,
      "text": "But in 2002, [Steven D&#39;Hondt] had convinced enough people"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 117909.0,
      "end_time": 121517.0,
      "text": "that he was on to something  that he actually got an expedition"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 121551.0,
      "end_time": 125730.0,
      "text": "on this drillship, called the JOIDES Resolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 125970.0,
      "end_time": 128176.0,
      "text": "And he ran it along with Bo Barker JÃ¸rgensen of Denmark."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 128201.0,
      "end_time": 129923.0,
      "text": "And so they were finally able to get"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 129947.0,
      "end_time": 133312.0,
      "text": "good pristine deep subsurface samples"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 133336.0,
      "end_time": 136149.0,
      "text": "some really without contamination from surface microbes."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 136173.0,
      "end_time": 141446.0,
      "text": "This drill ship is capable of drilling thousands of meters underneath the ocean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 141470.0,
      "end_time": 144966.0,
      "text": "and the mud comes up in sequential cores, one after the other --"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 144990.0,
      "end_time": 147660.0,
      "text": "long, long cores that look like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 147684.0,
      "end_time": 151493.0,
      "text": "This is being carried by scientists such as myself who go on these ships,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 151517.0,
      "end_time": 154517.0,
      "text": "and we process the cores on the ships and then we send them home"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 154541.0,
      "end_time": 156640.0,
      "text": "to our home laboratories for further study."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 156664.0,
      "end_time": 158141.0,
      "text": "So when John and his colleagues"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 158165.0,
      "end_time": 161720.0,
      "text": "got these first precious deep-sea pristine samples,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 161744.0,
      "end_time": 163625.0,
      "text": "they put them under the microscope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 163649.0,
      "end_time": 167758.0,
      "text": "and they saw images that looked pretty much like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 167782.0,
      "end_time": 170259.0,
      "text": "which is actually taken from a more recent expedition"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 170283.0,
      "end_time": 172469.0,
      "text": "by my PhD student, Joy Buongiorno."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 172493.0,
      "end_time": 174781.0,
      "text": "You can see the hazy stuff in the background."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 174805.0,
      "end_time": 177590.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s mud. That&#39;s deep-sea ocean mud,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 177614.0,
      "end_time": 181601.0,
      "text": "and the bright green dots stained with the green fluorescent dye"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 181625.0,
      "end_time": 184363.0,
      "text": "are real, living microbes."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 185173.0,
      "end_time": 188203.0,
      "text": "Now I&#39;ve got to tell you something really tragic about microbes."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 188227.0,
      "end_time": 190306.0,
      "text": "They all look the same under a microscope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 190330.0,
      "end_time": 191937.0,
      "text": "I mean, to a first approximation."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 191961.0,
      "end_time": 195553.0,
      "text": "You can take the most fascinating organisms in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 195577.0,
      "end_time": 199243.0,
      "text": "like a microbe that literally breathes uranium,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 199267.0,
      "end_time": 201679.0,
      "text": "and another one that makes rocket fuel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 201703.0,
      "end_time": 203259.0,
      "text": "mix them up with some ocean mud,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 203283.0,
      "end_time": 205480.0,
      "text": "put them underneath a microscope,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 205504.0,
      "end_time": 207315.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re just little dots."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 207339.0,
      "end_time": 208770.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s really annoying."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 208794.0,
      "end_time": 211285.0,
      "text": "So we can&#39;t use their looks to tell them apart."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 211309.0,
      "end_time": 213469.0,
      "text": "We have to use DNA, like a fingerprint,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 213493.0,
      "end_time": 215214.0,
      "text": "to say who is who."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 215238.0,
      "end_time": 217500.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;ll teach you guys how to do it right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 217524.0,
      "end_time": 221540.0,
      "text": "So I made up some data, and I&#39;m going to show you some data that are not real."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 221564.0,
      "end_time": 223747.0,
      "text": "This is to illustrate what it would look like"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 223771.0,
      "end_time": 227150.0,
      "text": "if a bunch of species were not related to each other at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 227722.0,
      "end_time": 230940.0,
      "text": "So you can see each species"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 230964.0,
      "end_time": 235163.0,
      "text": "has a list of combinations of A, G, C and T,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 235187.0,
      "end_time": 236902.0,
      "text": "which are the four sub-units of DNA,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 236926.0,
      "end_time": 240710.0,
      "text": "sort of randomly jumbled, and nothing looks like anything else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 240735.0,
      "end_time": 243346.0,
      "text": "and these species are totally unrelated to each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 243370.0,
      "end_time": 245425.0,
      "text": "But this is what real DNA looks like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 245449.0,
      "end_time": 247900.0,
      "text": "from a gene that these species happen to share."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 248477.0,
      "end_time": 251465.0,
      "text": "Everything lines up nearly perfectly."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 251489.0,
      "end_time": 254909.0,
      "text": "The chances of getting so many of those vertical columns"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 254933.0,
      "end_time": 258322.0,
      "text": "where every species has a C or every species has a T,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 258346.0,
      "end_time": 261131.0,
      "text": "by random chance, are infinitesimal."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 261154.0,
      "end_time": 266680.0,
      "text": "So we know that all those species had to have had a common ancestor."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 266920.0,
      "end_time": 267989.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re all relatives of each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 268130.0,
      "end_time": 269861.0,
      "text": "So now I&#39;ll tell you who they are."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 270338.0,
      "end_time": 272942.0,
      "text": "The top two are us and chimpanzees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 272966.0,
      "end_time": 276561.0,
      "text": "which y&#39;all already knew were related, because, I mean, obviously."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 276585.0,
      "end_time": 278440.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 278690.0,
      "end_time": 280847.0,
      "text": "But we&#39;re also related to things that we don&#39;t look like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 280871.0,
      "end_time": 285394.0,
      "text": "like pine trees and Giardia, which is that gastrointestinal disease"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 285418.0,
      "end_time": 288425.0,
      "text": "you can get if you don&#39;t filter your water while you&#39;re hiking."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 288449.0,
      "end_time": 293363.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re also related to bacteria like E. coli and Clostridium difficile,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 293387.0,
      "end_time": 296849.0,
      "text": "which is a horrible, opportunistic pathogen that kills lots of people."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 296873.0,
      "end_time": 301460.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s of course good microbes too, like Dehalococcoides ethenogenes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 301710.0,
      "end_time": 303939.0,
      "text": "which cleans up our industrial waste for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 303963.0,
      "end_time": 306702.0,
      "text": "So if I take these DNA sequences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 306726.0,
      "end_time": 309869.0,
      "text": "and then I use them, the similarities and differences between them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 309893.0,
      "end_time": 311722.0,
      "text": "to make a family tree for all of us"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 311746.0,
      "end_time": 313611.0,
      "text": "so you can see who is closely related,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 313635.0,
      "end_time": 315539.0,
      "text": "then this is what it looks like."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 315564.0,
      "end_time": 317847.0,
      "text": "So you can see clearly, at a glance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 317871.0,
      "end_time": 323188.0,
      "text": "that things like us and Giardia and bunnies and pine trees"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 323212.0,
      "end_time": 324988.0,
      "text": "are all, like, siblings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 325120.0,
      "end_time": 328920.0,
      "text": "and then the bacteria are like our ancient cousins."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 328116.0,
      "end_time": 332289.0,
      "text": "But we&#39;re kin to every living thing on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 332313.0,
      "end_time": 334781.0,
      "text": "So in my job, on a daily basis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 334805.0,
      "end_time": 339136.0,
      "text": "I get to produce scientific evidence against existential loneliness."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 339160.0,
      "end_time": 342240.0,
      "text": "So when we got these first DNA sequences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 342480.0,
      "end_time": 346248.0,
      "text": "from the first cruise, of pristine samples from the deep subsurface,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 346272.0,
      "end_time": 348121.0,
      "text": "we wanted to know where they were."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 348145.0,
      "end_time": 351359.0,
      "text": "So the first thing that we discovered is that they were not aliens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 351383.0,
      "end_time": 354967.0,
      "text": "because we could get their DNA to line up with everything else on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 354992.0,
      "end_time": 358190.0,
      "text": "But now check out where they go on our tree of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 359468.0,
      "end_time": 362570.0,
      "text": "The first thing you&#39;ll notice is that there&#39;s a lot of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 362594.0,
      "end_time": 364419.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t just one little species"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 364443.0,
      "end_time": 366562.0,
      "text": "that managed to live in this horrible place."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 366586.0,
      "end_time": 368690.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s kind of a lot of things."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 368930.0,
      "end_time": 370510.0,
      "text": "And the second thing that you&#39;ll notice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 370750.0,
      "end_time": 374895.0,
      "text": "hopefully, is that they&#39;re not like anything we&#39;ve ever seen before."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 375482.0,
      "end_time": 377616.0,
      "text": "They are as different from each other"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 377640.0,
      "end_time": 380505.0,
      "text": "as they are from anything that we&#39;ve known before"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 380529.0,
      "end_time": 382490.0,
      "text": "as we are from pine trees."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 382514.0,
      "end_time": 385695.0,
      "text": "So John Parkes was completely correct."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 386180.0,
      "end_time": 390847.0,
      "text": "He, and we, had discovered a completely new and highly diverse"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 390871.0,
      "end_time": 392841.0,
      "text": "microbial ecosystem on Earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 392865.0,
      "end_time": 396706.0,
      "text": "that no one even knew existed before the 1980s."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 397159.0,
      "end_time": 398692.0,
      "text": "So now we were on a roll."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 398716.0,
      "end_time": 403428.0,
      "text": "The next step was to grow these exotic species in a petri dish"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 403452.0,
      "end_time": 405622.0,
      "text": "so that we could do real experiments on them"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 405646.0,
      "end_time": 407685.0,
      "text": "like microbiologists are supposed to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 408900.0,
      "end_time": 409650.0,
      "text": "But no matter what we fed them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 409675.0,
      "end_time": 411238.0,
      "text": "they refused to grow."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 411825.0,
      "end_time": 415832.0,
      "text": "Even now, 15 years and many expeditions later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 415856.0,
      "end_time": 421260.0,
      "text": "no human has ever gotten a single one of these exotic deep subsurface microbes"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 421284.0,
      "end_time": 422947.0,
      "text": "to grow in a petri dish."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 422971.0,
      "end_time": 424657.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s not for lack of trying."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 425185.0,
      "end_time": 427161.0,
      "text": "That may sound disappointing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 427185.0,
      "end_time": 428908.0,
      "text": "but I actually find it exhilarating,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 428932.0,
      "end_time": 432503.0,
      "text": "because it means there are so many tantalizing unknowns to work on."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 432527.0,
      "end_time": 436114.0,
      "text": "Like, my colleagues and I got what we thought was a really great idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 436138.0,
      "end_time": 439419.0,
      "text": "We were going to read their genes like a recipe book,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 439443.0,
      "end_time": 442919.0,
      "text": "find out what it was they wanted to eat and put it in their petri dishes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 442944.0,
      "end_time": 444855.0,
      "text": "and then they would grow and be happy."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 444879.0,
      "end_time": 446530.0,
      "text": "But when we looked at their genes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 446554.0,
      "end_time": 450621.0,
      "text": "it turns out that what they wanted to eat was the food we were already feeding them."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 450646.0,
      "end_time": 452256.0,
      "text": "So that was a total wash."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 452280.0,
      "end_time": 455256.0,
      "text": "There was something else that they wanted in their petri dishes"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 455281.0,
      "end_time": 457970.0,
      "text": "that we were just not giving them."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 458248.0,
      "end_time": 461954.0,
      "text": "So by combining measurements from many different places"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 461978.0,
      "end_time": 463136.0,
      "text": "around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 463160.0,
      "end_time": 466823.0,
      "text": "my colleagues at the University of Southern California,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 466847.0,
      "end_time": 468553.0,
      "text": "Doug LaRowe and Jan Amend,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 468577.0,
      "end_time": 473280.0,
      "text": "were able to calculate that each one of these deep-sea microbial cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 473304.0,
      "end_time": 476669.0,
      "text": "requires only one zeptowatt of power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 476694.0,
      "end_time": 480634.0,
      "text": "and before you get your phones out, a zepto is 10 to the minus 21,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 480658.0,
      "end_time": 482706.0,
      "text": "because I know I would want to look that up."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 482730.0,
      "end_time": 484261.0,
      "text": "Humans, on the other hand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 484285.0,
      "end_time": 486874.0,
      "text": "require about 100 watts of power."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 486898.0,
      "end_time": 490409.0,
      "text": "So 100 watts is basically if you take a pineapple"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 490433.0,
      "end_time": 496643.0,
      "text": "and drop it from about waist height to the ground 881,632 times a day."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 496667.0,
      "end_time": 499470.0,
      "text": "If you did that and then linked it up to a turbine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 499720.0,
      "end_time": 502310.0,
      "text": "that would create enough power to make me happen for a day."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 503177.0,
      "end_time": 505970.0,
      "text": "A zeptowatt, if you put it in similar terms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 505994.0,
      "end_time": 510770.0,
      "text": "is if you take just one grain of salt"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 510101.0,
      "end_time": 513719.0,
      "text": "and then you imagine a tiny, tiny, little ball"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 513743.00000000006,
      "end_time": 517359.00000000006,
      "text": "that is one thousandth of the mass of that one grain of salt"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 517383.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520192.00000000006,
      "text": "and then you drop it one nanometer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 520216.0,
      "end_time": 524398.0,
      "text": "which is a hundred times smaller than the wavelength of visible light,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 524422.0,
      "end_time": 526570.0,
      "text": "once per day."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 526773.0,
      "end_time": 529971.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s all it takes to make these microbes live."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 530717.0,
      "end_time": 536820.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s less energy than we ever thought would be capable of supporting life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 536106.0,
      "end_time": 539180.0,
      "text": "but somehow, amazingly, beautifully,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 539204.0,
      "end_time": 540394.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 541370.0,
      "end_time": 543203.0,
      "text": "So if these deep-subsurface microbes"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 543227.0,
      "end_time": 546779.0,
      "text": "have a very different relationship with energy than we previously thought,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 546803.0,
      "end_time": 548767.0,
      "text": "then it follows that they&#39;ll have to have"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 548791.0,
      "end_time": 550948.0,
      "text": "a different relationship with time as well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 550972.0,
      "end_time": 554670.0,
      "text": "because when you live on such tiny energy gradients,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 554910.0,
      "end_time": 555786.0,
      "text": "rapid growth is impossible."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 555810.0,
      "end_time": 558827.0,
      "text": "If these things wanted to colonize our throats and make us sick,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 558851.0,
      "end_time": 561471.0,
      "text": "they would get muscled out by fast-growing streptococcus"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 561495.0,
      "end_time": 563656.0,
      "text": "before they could even initiate cell division."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 563680.0,
      "end_time": 566441.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s why we never find them in our throats."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 567537.0,
      "end_time": 571712.0,
      "text": "Perhaps the fact that the deep subsurface is so boring"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 571736.0,
      "end_time": 574226.0,
      "text": "is actually an asset to these microbes."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 574250.0,
      "end_time": 576338.0,
      "text": "They never get washed out by a storm."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 576362.0,
      "end_time": 578526.0,
      "text": "They never get overgrown by weeds."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 579125.0,
      "end_time": 582321.0,
      "text": "All they have to do is exist."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 582807.0,
      "end_time": 586817.0,
      "text": "Maybe that thing that we were missing in our petri dishes"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 586841.0,
      "end_time": 588562.0,
      "text": "was not food at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 588586.0,
      "end_time": 590640.0,
      "text": "Maybe it wasn&#39;t a chemical."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 590880.0,
      "end_time": 591914.0,
      "text": "Maybe the thing that they really want,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 591938.0,
      "end_time": 594770.0,
      "text": "the nutrient that they want, is time."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 596950.0,
      "end_time": 599671.0,
      "text": "But time is the one thing that I&#39;ll never be able to give them."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 599695.0,
      "end_time": 602909.0,
      "text": "So even if I have a cell culture that I pass to my PhD students,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 602933.0,
      "end_time": 605424.0,
      "text": "who pass it to their PhD students, and so on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 605448.0,
      "end_time": 608160.0,
      "text": "we&#39;d have to do that for thousands of years"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 608400.0,
      "end_time": 611271.0,
      "text": "in order to mimic the exact conditions of the deep subsurface,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 611295.0,
      "end_time": 613613.0,
      "text": "all without growing any contaminants."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 613638.0,
      "end_time": 614936.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just not possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 615637.0,
      "end_time": 618762.0,
      "text": "But maybe in a way we already have grown them in our petri dishes."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 618787.0,
      "end_time": 621597.0,
      "text": "Maybe they looked at all that food we offered them and said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 621621.0,
      "end_time": 623483.0,
      "text": "\"Thanks, I&#39;m going to speed up so much"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 623507.0,
      "end_time": 625747.0,
      "text": "that I&#39;m going to make a new cell next century."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 625771.0,
      "end_time": 626931.0,
      "text": "Ugh."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 626956.0,
      "end_time": 627995.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 628190.0,
      "end_time": 633128.0,
      "text": "So why is it that the rest of biology moves so fast?"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 633152.0,
      "end_time": 635580.0,
      "text": "Why does a cell die after a day"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 635820.0,
      "end_time": 637593.0,
      "text": "and a human dies after only a hundred years?"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 637617.0,
      "end_time": 640580.0,
      "text": "These seem like really arbitrarily short limits"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 640820.0,
      "end_time": 643810.0,
      "text": "when you think about the total amount of time in the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 643105.0,
      "end_time": 645916.0,
      "text": "But these are not arbitrary limits."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 645940.0,
      "end_time": 648831.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re dictated by one simple thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 648855.0,
      "end_time": 650914.0,
      "text": "and that thing is the Sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 651785.0,
      "end_time": 654535.0,
      "text": "Once life figured out how to harness the energy of the Sun"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 654559.0,
      "end_time": 655721.0,
      "text": "through photosynthesis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 655745.0,
      "end_time": 658664.0,
      "text": "we all had to speed up and get on day and night cycles."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 658688.0,
      "end_time": 662420.0,
      "text": "In that way, the Sun gave us both a reason to be fast"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 662660.0,
      "end_time": 663673.0,
      "text": "and the fuel to do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 663697.0,
      "end_time": 666556.0,
      "text": "You can view most of life on Earth like a circulatory system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 666580.0,
      "end_time": 668270.0,
      "text": "and the Sun is our beating heart."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 669640.0,
      "end_time": 671896.0,
      "text": "But the deep subsurface is like a circulatory system"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 671921.0,
      "end_time": 674356.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s completely disconnected from the Sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 674380.0,
      "end_time": 678872.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s instead being driven by long, slow geological rhythms."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 679933.0,
      "end_time": 685321.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s currently no theoretical limit on the lifespan of one single cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 686632.0,
      "end_time": 690599.0,
      "text": "As long as there is at least a tiny energy gradient to exploit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 690624.0,
      "end_time": 692808.0,
      "text": "theoretically, a single cell could live"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 692832.0,
      "end_time": 694974.0,
      "text": "for hundreds of thousands of years or more,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 694998.0,
      "end_time": 697442.0,
      "text": "simply by replacing broken parts over time."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 698470.0,
      "end_time": 702380.0,
      "text": "To ask a microbe that lives like that to grow in our petri dishes"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 702404.0,
      "end_time": 707467.0,
      "text": "is to ask them to adapt to our frenetic, Sun-centric, fast way of living,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 707491.0,
      "end_time": 709984.0,
      "text": "and maybe they&#39;ve got better things to do than that."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 710800.0,
      "end_time": 711317.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 711341.0,
      "end_time": 715618.0,
      "text": "Imagine if we could figure out how they managed to do this."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 715642.0,
      "end_time": 718928.0,
      "text": "What if it involves some cool, ultra-stable compounds"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 718952.0,
      "end_time": 721213.0,
      "text": "that we could use to increase the shelf life"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 721237.0,
      "end_time": 723824.0,
      "text": "in biomedical or industrial applications?"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 723848.0,
      "end_time": 726404.0,
      "text": "Or maybe if we figure out the mechanism that they use"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 726428.0,
      "end_time": 729546.0,
      "text": "to grow so extraordinarily slowly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 729570.0,
      "end_time": 732920.0,
      "text": "we could mimic it in cancer cells and slow runaway cell division."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 733928.0,
      "end_time": 735118.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 735142.0,
      "end_time": 738173.0,
      "text": "I mean, honestly, that is all speculation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 738197.0,
      "end_time": 740646.0,
      "text": "but the only thing I know for certain"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 740670.0,
      "end_time": 744742.0,
      "text": "is that there are a hundred billion billion billlion"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 744767.0,
      "end_time": 746871.0,
      "text": "living microbial cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 746895.0,
      "end_time": 749930.0,
      "text": "underlying all the world&#39;s oceans."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 749117.0,
      "end_time": 753482.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s 200 times more than the total biomass of humans on this planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 753966.0,
      "end_time": 757672.0,
      "text": "And those microbes have a fundamentally different relationship"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 757696.0,
      "end_time": 759561.0,
      "text": "with time and energy than we do."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 759989.0,
      "end_time": 762231.0,
      "text": "What seems like a day to them"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 762255.0,
      "end_time": 764572.0,
      "text": "might be a thousand years to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 765720.0,
      "end_time": 767910.0,
      "text": "They don&#39;t care about the Sun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 767115.0,
      "end_time": 769326.0,
      "text": "and they don&#39;t care about growing fast,"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 769350.0,
      "end_time": 772247.0,
      "text": "and they probably don&#39;t give a damn about my petri dishes ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 772271.0,
      "end_time": 773294.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 773334.0,
      "end_time": 777260.0,
      "text": "but if we can continue to find creative ways to study them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 777284.0,
      "end_time": 783619.0,
      "text": "then maybe we&#39;ll finally figure out what life, all of life, is like on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 784310.0,
      "end_time": 785181.0,
